ACTION:
With the system powered and the lamp off, measure the voltage on the control module INPUT pair (the two cables from the PSU) at the module terminals, then trace inside the control box and measure the voltage at the node feeding the relay contacts (the point after any series indicator LED/resistor and before the relay). Compare these to the PSU output. This will reveal whether there is a large voltage drop or open/short fault inside the control module ahead of the relay contacts that is clamping the output to about 0.36 V.
