description: With the system powered and the lamp off, measure the voltage on the control module INPUT pair (the two cables from the PSU) at the module terminals, then trace inside the control box and measure the voltage at the node feeding the relay contacts (the point after any series indicator LED/resistor and before the relay). Compare these to the PSU output. This will reveal whether there is a large voltage drop or open/short fault inside the control module ahead of the relay contacts that is clamping the output to about 0.36 V., outcome='PSU output and control input cables show matching polarities and voltages: PSU Output Cable (+) and Control Input Cable (+) are at ~11.99 V, and PSU Output Cable (−) and Control Input Cable (−) are at ~0 V, with no POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED. The PSU status LED and its series resistor drop about 10.7 V total (11.99 V to 1.29 V at the resistor, 1.29 V to 0 V across the LED), which is consistent with the measured readings. At the control relay, the feed side is at ~11.99 V and the other side is at ~0.36 V.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=155.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module ground / negative rail path,
description: With the system powered and lamp off, measure continuity (ohms) and then live DC voltage along the control module’s negative/return path: from the Control Input Cable (−) terminal to (1) the internal ground reference of the sensor/logic, (2) the relay coil return, and (3) the Control Output Cable (−) terminal. Look for any unexpected series resistance, diode junctions, or voltage drops that could leave the relay contact’s ‘0 V’ side sitting at ~0.36 V instead of true ground., outcome='Continuity on the Control Input Cable (−), Sensor Bias Resistor, Control Relay, and Control Output Cable (−) is nominal, with no unexpected series resistance indicated. Live measurements show the Control Input Cable (−) and Control Output Cable (−) sitting essentially at 0 V, while the sensor/logic reference is at ~0.12 V and the relay coil return is at ~0.36 V relative to ground. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED in the measured negative/return path connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=165.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient light sensor / threshold network in control module,
description: With the system powered and lamp off, probe the voltage at the sensor/logic input node (the junction between the light sensor, its bias network, and the comparator input) relative to the control module’s negative rail. Slowly vary ambient light over the sensor and observe whether this node voltage and the comparator output change state appropriately, or whether the sensor node is stuck at a nearly fixed level (~0.12–0.36 V above ground) regardless of illumination and pot settings., outcome='The sensor/logic input node is sitting near ground at the light sensor side (≈0.12 V) and is biased from the supply through the sensor bias resistor (≈12 V to 0.12 V), while the control relay output is at a higher low‑level (≈0.36 V). Across all measurements, no polarity inversion between (+) and (−) labeled connections is indicated.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module internal supply / reference ground connection to PSU negative,
description: With the system powered and lamp off, measure DC voltage directly between the control module’s internal logic/relay-reference ground node (the point used as ‘ground’ for the comparator and relay driver) and the PSU/output cable negative (true 0 V). Check for any steady offset (≈0.1–0.4 V). Then, with power off, measure resistance between this internal reference node and the Control Input Cable (−). This will detect a misplaced series element, bad ground reference, or wiring error that leaves the entire control electronics floating above true ground., outcome='The control module’s internal logic/relay-reference ground is offset by approximately 0.36 V relative to the PSU/output cable negative (true 0 V). Continuity tests show the control relay and the Control Input Cable (−) both have nominal resistance values.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
